# Linear Agentic Loop

## Evaluate
- Use Linear MCP `list_issues` filtered to the requested phase/milestone.
- Keep issues in Todo or In Progress; prioritize using this order:
  1) User-specified focus (phase/milestone, explicit issue IDs, or “do X next”).
  2) Dependencies: unblockers first, then work that has no blockers.
  3) Status: In Progress before Todo; avoid “Under Review” unless asked.
  4) Priority field: Urgent > High > Medium > Low.
  5) Smallest viable work that completes a slice and passes quality gates based on roadmap.
- Present a numbered list and identify the next actionable issue.

## Execute
- Move the chosen issue to In Progress with `update_issue`.
- Read the issue description, comments, and any linked docs before coding.
- Stop and review plan with me. Make an assessment of what might be incomplete information, illogical, dependency breaking. If an implementation is missing a dependency, highlight this.
- Implement changes following repo conventions (branch prefix `codex/`).
- Run quality gates: backend `pytest`, frontend `npm run lint`, plus relevant integration tests.
- If gates pass: summarize for me. Ask me if you should move issue to Done and add a summary comment to the issue.
- If gates fail: fix, re-run, and only then mark Done.

## Checkpoint
- Summarize files changed and tests run.
- Show remaining issues in the phase.
- Ask whether to continue to the next issue or stop.

## Guardrails
- Never commit or push without explicit user approval.
- Never modify issues outside the requested phase.
- If an issue is too large, ambiguous, or doesn't have concrete guidance, mark Blocked with a comment and move on.
